"""
Excerise 43: Faces on Money

It is common for images of a country's previous leader, or other individuals of historical
significance, to appear on its money. The inidividuals that appear on banknotes in the US are:

    individual                  Amount

    George Washington           $1
    Thomas Jefferson            $2
    Abraham Lincoln             $5
    Alexander Hamilton          $10
    Andrew Jackson              $20
    Ulysses S. Grant            $50
    Benjamin Franklin           $100

Write a program that begins by reading the denomination of a banknote from the user. Then
your program should display the name of the individual that appears on the banknote
of the entered amount. An appropriate error message should be displayed if no such note exists.

"""

user_in = int(input("Enter the amount (in $): "))

if user_in == 1:
    print("${} has George Washington.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 2:
    print("${} has Thomas Jefferson.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 5:
    print("${} has Abraham Lincoln.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 10:
    print("${} has Alexander Hamilton.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 20:
    print("${} has Andrew Jackson.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 50:
    print("${} has Ulysses S.Grant.".format(user_in))
    
elif user_in == 100:
    print("${} has Benjamin Franklin.".format(user_in))
    
else:
    print("No such denomination exists!")

    
